<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Additionally, in December 2021, we amended our Compensation Committee Charter to explicitly state that the </font><font style="color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Compensation </font><font style="color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Committee will review and oversee human capital management practices relating to our employees. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.17%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our commitment to a safe workplace starts with training and prevention. We require every employee to review and acknowledge our Code of Business Ethics and Policy Against Discrimination &amp; Harassment in the Workplace, and they are required to participate in an in-depth and interactive anti-harassment and anti-discrimination&#160;training. New employees receive their anti-harassment and discrimination training during new hire orientation. Collectively, this ensures that all employees understand how to create and promote a respectful workplace, assess potential situations sooner and escalate appropriately.&#160;&#160;&#8203;In 2021, as part of our continued commitment to providing a safe and inclusive workplace we re-doubled our efforts to educate employees and managers as part of our &#8220;Respectful Recharge&#8221; program, where employees received additional training on workplace expectations, consequences for violating Tesla&#8217;s policies and avenues to raise concerns without fear of retaliation.&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.17%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">While our goal is&#160;always prevention, reported complaints of discrimination and harassment are promptly investigated and if substantiated, subject to appropriate remedial measures up&#160;to and including termination. We have a dedicated team of Employee Relations partners who conduct impartial investigations into employee concerns and support overall positive workforce engagement. We encourage employees to raise concerns internally or externally. An employee can raise concerns or complaints to any member of&#160;management, Human Resources or Employee Relations. If they prefer to report another way, the Integrity Line is available to every employee globally, 24 hours a day, seven&#160;days a week. The Integrity Line allows employees to report concerns anonymously and without fear of retaliation.&#160;Human Resources, together with Employee Relations, will ensure that employee concerns are investigated promptly and impartially&#160;in a manner appropriate to the circumstances. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.17%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We remain confident in our commitment to creating and maintaining a respectful and inclusive workplace, and the steps we have taken to prevent and address harassment and discrimination throughout our workforce. We believe that our active Board oversight, existing policies and dedicated team effectively address the issues targeted by this proposal.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board recommends a vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the stockholder proposal regarding annual reporting on anti-harassment and discrimination efforts. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">25</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_EIGHT_8"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_EIGHT_8"></a>PROPOSAL EIGHT</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING ANNUAL REPORTING ON BOARD DIVERSITY</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEM_8"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEM_8"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Racial and Gender Board Diversity Report </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Whereas<font style="font-weight:normal;">: Our nation's racial reckoning and coronavirus's illumination of vast social inequities has led companies to reevaluate their diversity, equity, and inclusion policies and goals. Board diversity is one important facet, as investors and companies recognize it can be accretive to long term value creation. Board diversity requirements, including Nasdaq's 2021 ruling and California's 2018 legislation, acknowledge the value of racially and gender diverse boards.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Research indicates board diversity is an important lever to increase shareholder value, resulting in higher revenues, higher Return on Assets, a more diverse workforce, enhanced corporate governance, and improved stakeholder relations.</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">Boston Consulting Group finds companies with greater board diversity had 19 percent higher revenues than competitors.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">International Monetary Fund finds substituting one man for one woman on a board is associated with higher Return on Assets.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">Credit Suisse finds as the percentage of women on the board increases, so does the percentage of women in leadership.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">The University of Toronto finds companies with greater board diversity are less prone to accounting mistakes, business controversies, and poor investment decisions.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">Harvard Law research finds companies may be better positioned to recognize and respond to the interests of diverse stakeholders.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In response to this research, <font style="font-style:italic;">61 percent of investors believe boards &#8220;should aim to reflect the company's customer base and the broader societies in which they operate by including directors drawn from racial and ethnic minority groups&#8221;</font> (Institutional Shareholder Services).</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla does not report its current gender or racial and ethnic board composition, but Tesla's board demographics appear largely disproportionate from its customer base. Bloomberg reports the Board of Directors is comprised of 22 percent women. The demographic makeup of the United States, used here as a proxy for Tesla's customer base, is comprised of 51 percent women and 42 percent minorities.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that a Board of Directors with racial and gender composition reflective of Tesla's customer base and/or regions in which it operates will more astutely minimize business risk, maximize opportunity, and increase shareholder value.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Resolved<font style="font-weight:normal;">: Shareholders request that Tesla report annually on its policies and practices to help ensure its elected Board of Directors attains racial and gender representation that is better aligned with the demographics of its customers and/or regions in which it operates.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The report should be prepared at reasonable cost, omitting proprietary information, litigation strategy and legal compliance information.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.81%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Supporting Statement<font style="font-weight:normal;">: A report adequate for investors could, with board discretion, include disclosure of:</font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">Board targets aligned with customer demographics (for example, using company's country/state headquarter demographics as a proxy)</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">Progress/challenges meeting racial and/or gender board diversity targets</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">Strategies or practices deployed to increase diversity of board candidates</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">26</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD_8"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD_8"></a>Opposing Stateme</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">nt of the Board</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board has considered this proposal and determined that it would not serve the best interests of Tesla or our stockholders.&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla is committed to Diversity, Equity and Inclusion (DEI) principles at all levels of our organization. We use a people-first and data-driven approach to champion DEI in our business and in the communities in which we operate. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In the &#8220;Process and Considerations for Nominating Board Candidates&#8221; section, our proxy statement already includes detailed disclosures about the criteria our Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee considers when nominating Board candidates. Diversity is included as one of the important factors. Two of the three directors we added in the past four years are gender, racially and/or ethnically diverse and the chairperson of our Board is a woman. In 2021 and 2022, we enhanced our disclosures by reporting the gender and racial composition of the Board in our Impact Report, and beginning in 2022 we have similarly made such disclosures in our proxy statement regarding Board diversity. In addition, to underscore our commitment to diversity and provide additional transparency, we began providing EEO-1 data for US employees in our Impact Report beginning in 2022. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Committee conducts annual evaluations of our Board effectiveness, providing it with an opportunity to examine whether our Board members have the right composition of skills and experiences. When identifying and recommending new candidates, the Committee continues to consider opportunities to increase our Board diversity in a way that supports the current and anticipated needs of the Company. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">For these reasons, we believe that the current scope of Tesla&#8217;s reporting is appropriate in that it provides stockholders with visibility into our Board demographics and the steps we have taken to successfully increase the Board&#8217;s diversity.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board recommends a vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the stockholder proposal regarding annual reporting on board diversity.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">27</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_NINE_9"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_NINE_9"></a>PROPOSAL NINE</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING REPORTING ON EMPLOYEE ARBITRATION</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT3"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT3"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">RESOLVED<font style="font-weight:normal;">:</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-right:2.41%;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Shareholders of Tesla, Inc. (&#8220;Tesla&#8221;) ask the Board of Directors to oversee the preparation of a publicly-disclosed report on the impact of the use of mandatory arbitration on Tesla&#8217;s brand, employees<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>workplace<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>culture.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>The<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>report<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>should<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>evaluate<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>the<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>impact<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>Tesla&#8217;s<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>current<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>use<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>of arbitration on the prevalence of harassment and discrimination in its workplace, on employees&#8217; ability<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>seek<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>redress,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>on<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>consumer<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>perceptions<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>Tesla<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>as<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>an<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>employer.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>The<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>report<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>should<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>be prepared at reasonable cost and omit proprietary and personal information.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">WHEREAS<font style="font-weight:normal;">:</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">A<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>workplace<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>that<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>tolerates<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>harassment<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>discrimination<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>invites<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>legal,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>brand,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>financial,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>human capital risk. Companies may experience reduced morale, lost productivity, absenteeism, and challenges<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>in<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>attracting<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>retaining<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>talent.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>A<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>number<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>studies<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>have<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>found<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>significant<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>share<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>value benefits associated with diverse, equitable and inclusive workplaces.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla requires employees to agree to arbitrate employment-related claims.<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>Mandatory arbitration limits<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>employees&#8217;<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>remedies<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>for<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>wrongdoing,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>reduces<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>employee<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>willingness<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>report<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>discrimination<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> and, per the U.S. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC), &#8220;can shield serial harassers from accountability and allow them to repeatedly abuse employees.&#8221;<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> Arbitration also prevents class-action suits, which may allow a sense of impunity for companies with poorly implemented or managed diversity, equity and inclusion policies.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">These<font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font>concerns<font style="letter-spacing:-0.5pt;"> </font>are<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>particularly<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>relevant<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>Tesla.<font style="letter-spacing:-1pt;"> </font>The<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>California&#8217;s<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>Department<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>Fair<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>Employment and Housing, which is not subject to Tesla&#8217;s arbitration provisions, announced in February 2022 that it would be suing Tesla after receiving hundreds of complaints and conducting a three-year investigation. Allegations include that employees were subjected to racial slurs; segregated and discriminated against in job assignments, pay, and promotion; and faced retaliation when they reported their experiences.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> This lawsuit joins numerous other allegations of racial or sexual harassment and discrimination at Tesla.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Ongoing use of employee arbitration creates a long-tail risk for Tesla, particularly as the company faces<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>a<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>changing<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>regulatory<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>landscape<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>with<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>the<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>passage<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>The<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>Ending<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>Forced<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>Arbitration<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>Sexual Assault<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>Sexual<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>Harassment<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>Act.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>This<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>Act<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>prohibits<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>the<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>use<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>arbitration<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>when<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>there<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>are<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>claims of sexual harassment. In addition, in California, employers are not allowed to retaliate against employees that refuse to sign arbitration agreements.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">A<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>number of companies have ceased, or never required, employees to arbitrate discrimination claims.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>This<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>includes<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>Adobe,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>AirBnb,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>Google,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>IBM,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>Intel,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>Microsoft,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>Salesforce<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>Uber,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>which<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>have relaxed<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>or<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>do<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>not<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>use<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>these<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>policies,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>as<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>well<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>as<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>Google,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>whose<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>use<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>arbitration<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>was<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>identified<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>as<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>a key aspect of a &#8220;culture of concealment&#8221; in its $310 million misconduct settlement.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">6</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla&#8217;s valuable brand would be harmed by an association with racist, sexist, or other discriminatory<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>behaviors.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>Its<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>future<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>success<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>also<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>relies<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>on<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>its<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>ability<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>innovate,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>implement those innovations effectively.<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>For investors to have confidence that it will be able to do this well, Tesla must also have confidence that the company has effective human capital management <font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;">systems.</font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<div align="left"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:20%;"><tr><td style="width:20%;"></td></tr><tr><td valign="top"  style="border-bottom:Solid 1pt #000000;"><p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">

<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:0%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup>&nbsp;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:none;color:#auto;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;">https://www.eeoc.gov/newsroom/eeoc-chair-applauds-passage-ending-forced-arbitration-</font><font style="text-decoration:none;color:#auto;letter-spacing:-0.25pt;">act</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:0%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup>&nbsp;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:none;color:#auto;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;">https://qz.com/2126548/why-is-california-suing-tesla/</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:0%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup>&nbsp;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:none;color:#auto;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;">https://www.reuters.com/business/autos-transportation/california-lawsuit-latest-accuse-tesla-discrimination-2022</font><font style="text-decoration:none;color:#auto;">-02-10/</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:0%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup>&nbsp;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:none;color:#auto;">https://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/california-s-mandatory-arbitration-ban-5885483/#:~:text=On%20September%2015%2C%202021%2C%20in,to%20sign%20an%20arbitration%20agreement</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:0%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">6</sup>&nbsp;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:none;color:#auto;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;">https://www.law.com/therecorder/2020/09/25/google-ends-mandatory-arbitration-in-310m-sexual-harassment-settlement/</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">28</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk35955841"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD6"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD3"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD6"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD3"></a>Opposing Statement of the Board</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;">The Board has considered this proposal and determined that it would not serve the best interests of Tesla or our stockholders. As with the similar proposal presented by this proponent at the 2020 and 2021 annual meetings of stockholders, both of which were rejected by Tesla&#8217;s stockholders, the proponent cites inaccurate and unsupported assertions regarding arbitration and its alleged impact on workplace conditions at Tesla.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;">Much of the proposal has been obviated due to a recent change in the law. As the proponent recognizes, the Ending Forced Arbitration of Sexual Assault and Sexual Harassment Act now prohibits employers from enforcing standard arbitration provisions for these types of claims that arise after the date of the law&#8217;s enactment. Tesla will fully comply with the new law and has already taken steps to amend the standard arbitration clause in its new hire agreement. Obviously, there is no need for Tesla to issue a report about the effects of arbitration on the existence of sexual harassment in the workplace when such claims will no longer be arbitrable, unless the employee so chooses.&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;">Still, </font>Congress has not ended arbitration for other types of workplace claims, and Tesla continues to believe that arbitration remains the best method for resolving such disputes. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;">The proponent incorrectly asserts that there is a connection between arbitration and workplace culture. Tesla has a zero-tolerance policy for harassment of any kind, and we have always disciplined and terminated employees who engage in misconduct, including those who use racial slurs or harass others in different ways. We have a dedicated Employee Relations team that responds to and investigates all such complaints. This year, we rolled out an additional training program that reinforces Tesla&#8217;s requirement that all employees must treat each other with respect and reminds employees about the numerous ways they can report concerns, including anonymously. Above all, Tesla continues to seek to provide a workplace that is safe, respectful, fair and inclusive&#8212;all of which are vital to achieving our mission.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Contrary to what the proponent claims, Tesla&#8217;s standard arbitration provision specifically states that the parties are entitled to all remedies available in a court of law. The fact that a claim is not adjudicated by a court or does not have certain procedural aspects does not mean that legal remedies are not available through arbitration. Arbitration offers an alternative form of adjudication by an experienced jurist selected with both parties&#8217; participation that is often quicker than a court trial, especially in jurisdictions where courts are overburdened. The overall expediency benefits both parties with a fair resolution and a speedier return to their respective priorities without miring them in lengthy litigation. The proponent fails to acknowledge that there are potential downsides to litigating matters in court, including costs associated with delays and the risk of jury verdicts that are untethered to the evidence presented and based on bias and emotion, rather than reality. Broken judicial systems may benefit plaintiff&#8217;s lawyers, but they do not benefit stockholders. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The proponent also fails to explain how arbitration prevents Tesla employees from learning about shared concerns or reduces willingness to report claims. Tesla has been built upon a culture of open communication, and employees have the right to freely discuss the terms and conditions of employment and to raise complaints internally or externally. An employee is free to publicize the results of an arbitration (as long as it excludes any trade secrets or proprietary business information), and to initiate a lawsuit by first filing a complaint in court. Arbitration does nothing to silence alleged victims.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As we pledged in our annual Impact Report, Tesla designed its workplace and policies to provide all employees with a respectful and safe working environment by not tolerating any discrimination, harassment, retaliation or any other mistreatment at work, whether based on a legally protected status or otherwise. On the other hand, the<font style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;">&#160;proponent&#8217;s one-size-fits-all goal appears to be that every company simply eliminate employee arbitration without considering such commitments and action.&#160;</font>The proponent makes conclusory statements about other companies and their arbitration policies without considering or specifying how such other companies may or may not be similarly situated to Tesla. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We reiterate that Tesla, its employees and its stockholders would be better served by continuing to execute on our mission and tangible workplace goals rather than devote attention and resources to reporting on an inaccurately characterized issue for which the proponent has identified no tangible benefit to Tesla, its workers or its stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board recommends a vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the stockholder proposal regarding reporting on employee arbitration.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">29</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_TEN"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_TEN"></a>PROPOSAL TEN</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING REPORTING ON LOBBYING</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT4"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT4"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">RESOLVED<font style="font-weight:normal;">:</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Shareholders</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">request</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">that</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">the</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Board</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">of</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Directors</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">conduct</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">an</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">evaluation</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and issue</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">a</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">report</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">(at</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">reasonable</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">cost,</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">omitting</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">proprietary</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">information)</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">describing</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">if,</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">how, Tesla Inc.&#8217;s (&#8220;Tesla&#8217;s&#8221;) lobbying and policy influence activities (direct and through trade associations and social welfare and nonprofit organizations) align with the Paris Agreement&#8217;s goal to limit average global warming to 1.5 degrees Celsius, and how Tesla plans to mitigate risks presented by any misalignment. The evaluation should examine underlying direct and indirect lobbying activities and not rely solely on publicly stated positions to determine</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">alignment with the Paris Agreement.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">SUPPORTING<font style="letter-spacing:2.3pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;">STATEMENT</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Recent reports highlight critical gaps between the climate commitments made by national governments and the actions necessary to prevent the worst effects of climate change.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> An April 2022 Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change assessment makes it clear that nations are not doing enough to limit global warming<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> to 1.5 degrees Celsius and that this goal is now almost entirely out of reach unless immediate and dramatic changes are implemented to limit fossil fuel use and re-envision energy, transport, and land development. Society now has just a slim chance of meeting this goal.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Companies like Tesla have a crucial role to play in empowering policymakers to close these gaps. Investors need clear information on how companies are taking action to do so, including an assessment of the alignment between companies&#8217; policy advocacy and both the goals of the Paris Agreement and companies&#8217; own climate commitments and policy advocacy.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Of particular concern is policy advocacy done by trade associations and other organizations that often present major obstacles to the implementation of climate policies. Companies may tout their own climate efforts, but often fail to account for their support for organizations and initiatives that work to block critical climate policies.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla wants to &#8220;accelerate the world&#8217;s transition to sustainable energy.&#8221;<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> Yet it is unclear how Tesla uses public policy engagement or other forms of lobbying to achieve this aim. Tesla&#8217;s 2020 Impact Report discusses neither its climate policy priorities, nor the policy strategies and goals that would assist Tesla in meeting its sustainable business objectives. Tesla does not appear to disclose the trade associations, business alliances, or social welfare organizations in which it participates. Tesla&#8217;s governance documents do not cover political engagement or lobbying and there is no mention of Board or executive oversight for lobbying activities in its Board Committee charters. It is therefore difficult for investors to determine if Tesla&#8217;s policy engagement aligns with the goals of the Paris Agreement and the Company&#8217;s own strategic business goals.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Corporate lobbying that is inconsistent with the goals of the Paris Agreement poses mounting systemic risks to our financial systems and infrastructure, as delays in curbing greenhouse gases increase physical risks from extreme weather, threaten regional economic stability, and heighten portfolio volatility.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">6</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> Proponents view fulfillment of the Paris Agreement as imperative because climate scenarios of 3 degrees Celsius or more are unacceptable and uninvestable.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>

<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:3.33%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">30</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD4"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD4"></a>Opposing Statement of the Board</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board has considered this proposal and determined that it would not serve the best interests of Tesla or our stockholders.&#8239; </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The stockholder proponent purports to care about curbing the worst effects of climate change, and yet chooses to devote its attention and criticisms on one of the most well-known and successful clean energy companies in the world. From day one, Tesla&#8217;s mission has been to accelerate the world&#8217;s transition to sustainable energy, and we have made substantial and concrete strides towards our goals. In 2021, the global fleet of Tesla vehicles, energy storage and solar panels enabled our customers to avoid emitting 8.4 million metric tons of CO2e. Unlike traditional automotive manufacturers, we have based the success of our entire business upon values that align with the Paris Agreement&#8217;s goal to limit global warming.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our political engagement and lobbying activities reflect our mission, and are directly focused on hastening the world&#8217;s transition to zero emission vehicles and expanding and prioritizing the use of renewable energy. To this end, we file publicly available federal Lobbying Disclosure Act Reports each quarter, which provide information about expenditures for the quarter, describes the specific legislation that was the topic of communications and identifies the individual who lobbied on our behalf. A simple online search by the stockholder proponent would provide it with the answers it seeks about our political engagement and lobbying activities.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Due to the importance public policy decisions will have on our strategies, operations and shareholder value, we have put in place certain practices and processes in order to ensure that our political engagement activities align with our mission. Our Senior Director of Government Relations and Policy directly reports to our Chief Executive Officer, and regularly reports on progress and initiatives to our Board members.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Because our existing disclosures already provide stockholders with ample information on our lobbying activities, and the alignment of Tesla&#8217;s mission and actions to the Paris Agreement, we believe that Tesla, its employees and its stockholders are better served by continuing to execute on our mission rather than devoting attention and resources to additional reporting.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board recommends a vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the stockholder proposal regarding reporting on lobbying.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">31</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_NINE"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_ELEVEN"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_NINE"></a>PROPOSA<a name="PROPOSAL_ELEVEN"></a>L ELEVEN</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING ADOPTION OF A FREEDOM OF ASSOCIATION AND COLLECTIVE BARGAINING POLICY</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT5"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT5"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">RESOLVED:<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">the</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Board</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">of</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Directors</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">of Tesla,</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Inc.</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">(&#8220;Tesla&#8221;</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">or</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">&#8220;the</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">company&#8221;)</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">to</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">adopt</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">publicly disclose a</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">policy</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">on</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">its commitment to respect the rights to freedom of association and collective bargaining in its operations, as reflected in the International Labour Organization (ILO) </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Declaration on Fundamental Principles and Rights at Work </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">(&#8220;Fundamental Principles&#8221;). The policy should:</font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#auto;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Be</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.25pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">applicable</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.25pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">to</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.25pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Tesla&#8217;s</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">direct</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.2pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">operations</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.2pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">and</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.3pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">subsidiaries</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;color:#000000;"> globally;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>

<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:0pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font
