style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">any violations of these rights, including how it will remedy any misaligned practices.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">SUPPORTING STATEMENT: <font style="font-weight:normal;">Freedom of association and collective bargaining are fundamental human rights protected by</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">national</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">international</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">legal</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">standards</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">including</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">the</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">ILO</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Fundamental</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Principles</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">the</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">UN</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Universal</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Declaration of Human Rights.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>ability<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>workers<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>organize,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>act<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>concertedly,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>engage<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>in<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>collective<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>bargaining<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>is<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>an<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>important<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>human<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>right<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>that can be a net positive for companies and investors.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Despite a recent public invitation<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>by the company&#8217;s CEO for labor unions to organize a vote at Tesla&#8217;s California factory without<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>interference,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>Tesla<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>does<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>not<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>have<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>any<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>formal<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>policy<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>commitments<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>respect<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>the<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>right<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>freedom<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>association, nor has it demonstrated how it would effectively operationalize such a commitment. While the Company&#8217;s Supplier Code of Conduct<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>articulates the Company&#8217;s expectations of suppliers in this regard, it has no corresponding policies for its own operations.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In fact, the Company has been accused of limiting the exercise of fundamental labor rights through tactics of interference,<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>intimidation,<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>and retaliation against employees involved in unionization efforts.<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>In 2021, the National Labor<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>Relations<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>Board<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>upheld<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>a<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>2019<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>ruling<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>that<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>Tesla<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>illegally<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>fired<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>a<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>worker<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>involved<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>in<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>union<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>organizing,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>that<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>the CEO had illegally threatened workers regarding unionization.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">These allegations, against the backdrop of claims of racial discrimination and sexual harassment<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">6</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>by former Tesla employees<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>reports<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>poor<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>working<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>conditions,<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">7</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>represent<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>material<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>reputational,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>legal<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>operational<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>risks<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>its shareholders.<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>Allegations of interference with unionization efforts, and resulting regulatory enforcement, at other<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">8</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>companies<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">9</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>further demonstrate the significance of these risks.</p>
<div align="left"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:20%;"><tr><td style="width:20%;"></td></tr><tr><td valign="top"  style="border-bottom:Solid 1pt #000000;"><p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p></td></tr></table></div>

<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:0%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">9</sup>&nbsp;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/starbucks-workers-say-anti-union-campaign-violated-u-s-law-1.1677087</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">32</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The transition to a low-carbon future cannot come at the expense of workers&#8217; rights. It is crucial for shareholders to understand how Tesla&#8217;s policies and practices respect fundamental labor rights. Greater transparency on these issues would help address concerns about the company&#8217;s reputation, clarify its commitment to basic human rights, enable investors<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>perform<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>their<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>own<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>due<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>diligence<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>according<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>their<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>fiduciary<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>duty<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>protect<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>long-term<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>shareholder<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>value.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>urge<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>fellow<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>shareholders<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>vote<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>FOR<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>this<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;">resolution.</font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD5"></a>O<a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD5"></a>pposing Statement of the Board</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board has considered this proposal and determined that it would not serve the best interests of Tesla or our stockholders.&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The ethical treatment of all people and regard for human rights is core to our mission of promoting a sustainable future. We endorse and base our definition of human rights on the United Nation's Universal Declaration for Human Rights (UDHR). The UDHR focuses&#160;on dignity, respect and equality, without discrimination, and recognizes the right to freedom of association and collective bargaining. Our commitment to human rights is so deeply ingrained in our values that we also require all of our suppliers to follow our Supplier Code of Conduct, which mandates our suppliers to respect the right of all workers to form and join trade unions of their own choosing, to bargain collectively, to engage in peaceful assembly, as well as respect the right of workers to refrain from such activities. Our suppliers must allow workers and/or their representatives to be able to openly communicate and share ideas and concerns with management regarding working conditions and management practices without fear of discrimination, reprisal, intimidation or harassment.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We have more than 100,000 employees worldwide, and we comply with all applicable local laws related to freedom of association and collective bargaining, and respect internationally recognized human rights in all the areas we operate. In Germany, where we have just opened Gigafactory Berlin, we have established a works council which advocates for employees and acts similarly to a union. In the US, we share information with employees on their rights under the National Labor Relations Act and we provide manager training on employee rights, including the freedom of association. These actions speak for themselves. The stockholder proponent is asking Tesla to expend resources to create and maintain a policy framework and additional administrative bureaucracy, which will not meaningfully alter Tesla&#8217;s commitment to human rights.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Along with our policies and the actions we have taken to protect our employees&#8217; rights, we also provide our employees multiple methods to report any concerns or grievances. Tesla has been built upon a culture of open communication, and employees have the right to freely discuss their wages, benefits and terms and conditions of employment. They also have the ability to raise complaints internally or externally. We encourage employees to bring any concerns or grievances they may have to any member of management or their HR partner. We also operate an Integrity Line, which is available 24 hours a day, seven days a week, for employees to anonymously report concerns without fear of retaliation. In addition, our global Take Charge program enables employees to report issues and suggestions on safety, security and work practices, with the option to report anonymously. All issues and suggestions are responded to and tracked to closure. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">A talented and engaged workforce is central to our mission to accelerate the world&#8217;s transition to sustainable energy. In order to recruit and retain this workforce, Tesla is committed to, among other things, regular and meaningful engagement with our employees, a robust culture of safety and highly competitive compensation programs. We offer wages and benefits that meet or exceed those of other comparable manufacturing jobs in the regions where we operate, and we recently increased our base pay even further. In addition, unlike other manufacturers, every single employee of our Company has the option of receiving equity, which can result in significantly higher compensation beyond our already industry-leading base compensation.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Therefore, as we believe that we have already included adequate disclosure with respect to employee rights, are actively engaged in protecting these rights, and have devoted substantial resources to creating a healthy culture, this proposal would not create additional benefits to our employees or value for our shareholders.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board recommends a vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the stockholder proposal regarding Adoption of a freedom of association and collective bargaining policy.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">33</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_TWELVE"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_TWELVE"></a>PROPOSAL TWELVE</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING ADDITIONAL REPORTING ON CHILD LABOR</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT6"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT6"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:8pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.33%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">End Child Labor in Electric Vehicle Battery Production</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:8pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.33%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2022-Tesla, Inc. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Resolved: <font style="font-weight:normal;">Shareholders request that the Board of Directors issue a public report, at reasonable cost and</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">omitting</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">proprietary</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">information,</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">describing</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">if,</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">how, Tesla&#8217;s</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">policies</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">practices governing</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.45pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">the sourcing</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">of</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.8pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">battery</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.8pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">minerals</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.35pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.75pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">progress</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.4pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">towards</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.45pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">cobalt-free</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.85pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">battery goals</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.35pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">will</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.95pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">put the Company on course to eradicate child labor in all forms from its battery supply chain by 2025. Reporting</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.95pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">is requested</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">within</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.85pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">one year from Tesla&#8217;s 2022 annual</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">meeting.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Whereas:<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Sourcing</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">cobalt</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">for</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">electric</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">vehicle</font><font style="letter-spacing:3.25pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">batteries</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">from</font><font style="letter-spacing:3.55pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">mining</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">companies</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">facing</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">ongoing allegations</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.7pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">of</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">child labor</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and poor</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">working</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">conditions poses material</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">risks</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">to Tesla.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup></font><font style="color:#000000;font-weight:normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font><font style="font-weight:normal;">The Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) supplies 70% of the world&#8217;s cobalt and child labor is</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">well documented</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.9pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">in artisanal</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">mines.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup></font><font style="color:#000000;font-weight:normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font><font style="font-weight:normal;">The</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">ILO</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.05pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">recognizes</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">cobalt</font><font style="letter-spacing:0.95pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">mining as</font><font style="letter-spacing:0.9pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">hazardous</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">work and one</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">of</font><font style="letter-spacing:0.85pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">the worst forms of child</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.65pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">labor, as children</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.7pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">work with sharp tools in mines at risk of collapse.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup></font><font style="color:#000000;font-weight:normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font><font style="font-weight:normal;">ILO Convention</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.7pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">182 calls for</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">urgent</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.15pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">action</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.35pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">to eliminate these forms,</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.3pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">and Sustainable</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.9pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Development</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.6pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">Goal</font><font style="letter-spacing:0.95pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">8.7</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.25pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">calls to end all</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">child</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">labor</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">by 2025; yet</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.8pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">voluntary</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">corporate</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">actions</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">have failed</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">to</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.9pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">eradicate</font><font style="letter-spacing:2pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">hazardous</font><font style="letter-spacing:1.9pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">child labor from cobalt mining.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup></font><font style="color:#000000;font-weight:normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Child labor in the cobalt supply chain exposes Tesla and its investors to financial, legal, and reputational risks. In 2019, a class action lawsuit was filed against Tesla and four technology companies for allegedly &#8220;aiding and abetting in the<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>death and serious injury of children<font style="letter-spacing:1.9pt;"> </font>who claim they<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>were working in cobalt mines in their<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>supply chain.&#8221;<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>In the<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>joint motion to dismiss, defendants did not challenge the fact that child labor is occurring in their cobalt supply chains, but argued that conduct by their suppliers is out of their control, which conflicts with Tesla&#8217;s policies that the<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>company<font style="letter-spacing:1.45pt;"> </font>claims<font style="letter-spacing:1.65pt;"> </font>prohibit<font style="letter-spacing:1.85pt;"> </font>its<font style="letter-spacing:0.75pt;"> </font>suppliers from<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>using<font style="letter-spacing:1.15pt;"> </font>child<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>labor.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">6</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>This<font style="letter-spacing:1.25pt;"> </font>argument<font style="letter-spacing:1.35pt;"> </font>disregards<font style="letter-spacing:1.5pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:1.3pt;"> </font>seeks to undermine corporate responsibilities for human rights impacts associated with business relationships<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>and the<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>power<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>buyers have to require adherence to a zero-tolerance policy for child labor,<font style="letter-spacing:0.1pt;"> </font>or<font style="letter-spacing:0.45pt;"> </font>risk<font style="letter-spacing:0.5pt;"> </font>being<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>dropped<font style="letter-spacing:0.95pt;"> </font>as<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>a<font style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt;"> </font>supplier.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">7</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> </sup></font>Plaintiffs<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>filed<font style="letter-spacing:0.8pt;"> </font>an<font style="letter-spacing:0.35pt;"> </font>appeal<font style="letter-spacing:0.45pt;"> </font>following<font style="letter-spacing:0.25pt;"> </font>the<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>2021<font style="letter-spacing:0.75pt;"> </font>court<font style="letter-spacing:0.65pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;">ruling.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">8</sup></font><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></font></p> <div></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">While Tesla reports on cobalt sourcing procedures, multistakeholder initiatives, and pilots, these disclosures<font style="letter-spacing:1.35pt;"> </font>fail<font style="letter-spacing:1.35pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:0.65pt;"> </font>demonstrate<font style="letter-spacing:1.2pt;"> </font>that<font style="letter-spacing:1.55pt;"> </font>its<font style="letter-spacing:1pt;"> </font>cobalt<font style="letter-spacing:0.75pt;"> </font>supply<font style="letter-spacing:0.95pt;"> </font>chain<font style="letter-spacing:1.95pt;"> </font>is free<font style="letter-spacing:0.85pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:1.35pt;"> </font>child<font style="letter-spacing:1.85pt;"> </font>labor.<font style="letter-spacing:1.35pt;"> </font>Investors<font style="letter-spacing:1.4pt;"> </font>will<font style="letter-spacing:2pt;"> </font>not have this assurance unless Tesla implements supplier <font style="font-style:italic;">requirements, </font>not expectations, that are binding,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font>enforceable,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>regularly<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>monitored<font style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt;"> </font>for<font style="letter-spacing:-0.75pt;"> </font>compliance<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>with<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>national and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>international laws prohibiting child labor and the company&#8217;s own<font style="letter-spacing:1.7pt;"> </font>policies.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>Tesla aims to phase out cobalt in its electric vehicle batteries and seeks to position itself as a socially responsible company, the company remains exposed to human rights risks in the<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>supply chains for other critical transition<font style="letter-spacing:1.85pt;"> </font>minerals.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">9</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></font></p> <div></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>

<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:0%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">9 </sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">https://www.business-humanrights.org/en/from-us/briefings/transition-minerals-sector-case-studies/human-rights-in-the-mineral-supply-chains-of-electric-vehicles/</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;margin-left:1.73%;text-indent:-1.73%;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">34</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU10"></a>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD_12"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD_12"></a>Opposing Statement of the Board</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board has considered this proposal and determined that it would not serve the best interests of Tesla or our stockholders.&#160;&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As we noted in response to the proposal requesting additional reporting regarding human rights that was presented by the same proponent at the 2021 annual meeting of stockholders, which was rejected by Tesla&#8217;s stockholders,&#160;Tesla&#8217;s annual Impact Report already describes how human rights values, including those related to child labor, are&#160;respected in our&#160;operations. The proponent&#8217;s justification for additional reporting on child labor appears to be based on legal proceedings that have been dismissed by the court, and the proponent uses the argument made by the defendants in their motion to dismiss to imply that Tesla, as a defendant, is not taking action to identify and eliminate child labor from its supply chain. In fact, protecting human rights is core to Tesla&#8217;s procurement strategy and the position taken in these proceedings that our actions could not have met the standard for legal causation does nothing to undermine that fact. Indeed, because Tesla recognizes the risk of human rights issues within global cobalt supply chains, we have established and implemented a supply chain due diligence management system aligned with the OECD Due Diligence Guidance for Responsible Mineral Supply Chains from Conflict-Affected and High-Risk Countries. We are one of the few downstream companies that publicly report through our Impact Report on how we follow each of the five steps set out in the Guidance, including how we identify (including through audits) and mitigate risks (for its part, the OECD has identified reporting on risk mitigation as being very weak across the industry). As stated in the Impact Report,&#160;in the event that&#160;modern slavery, child labor or human trafficking is identified in our supply chain and has not been remediated by the supplier within a reasonable time&#160;frame, Tesla will transition away from that supplier. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Based on the risk identification procedures mentioned below and described more fully in our Impact Report, Tesla does in fact disclose in our Impact Report that we have found no evidence to date of Tesla causing, contributing to or being linked to child labor, modern slavery or human trafficking in our supply chain. In fact, we can be more confident of this than other OEMs due to our unique sourcing strategy: Rather than relying on companies that typically sit between OEMs and mining companies, we source our cobalt directly from mine sites. This means we can be more confident about where our cobalt comes from and can confirm, based on best practice risk identification, that we do not source from artisanal and small-scale mining (ASM), which is typically at risk of child labor. Rather, we source our cobalt from industrial mines, where no child labor has been identified to date. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In addition, we conduct our own audits of the mine sites and refiners in our cobalt supply chain and review results from third-party industry audit programs such as the Responsible Minerals Initiative (RMI)&#8217;s Responsible Minerals Assurance Process (RMAP). In 2021, 83% of refiners and mine sites in Tesla&#8217;s battery supply chain either underwent or committed to undergo independent external sustainability audits against RMAP and responsible mining standards. This was complemented by our own audits that assessed how specific cobalt and precursor suppliers conducted due diligence on their supply chain on OECD Annex II risks, which include child labor. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In 2021, a Tesla delegation conducted an on-the-ground assessment on environmental and social conditions in the DRC. While we do not source from ASM, the trip to the DRC helped us understand the importance of ASM for local livelihoods. This is why we fund and sit on the Steering Committee of the Fair Cobalt Alliance (FCA), a multi-stakeholder initiative to support the improvement of conditions in communities impacted by ASM. One of the achievements of the FCA is the development of referral system for children engaged in mining activities, including child labor notification protocol, remediation solution packages, and guidelines for case managers on remediation steps, and trainings related to child rights. One of the reasons for this support is to show that &#8211; despite not having identified it in our supply chain &#8211; we understand that child labor is an existing challenge in the DRC that requires structural solutions. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla remains confident in our efforts and commitment to ensuring child labor is not part of our supply chain, and that our publicly available policies and disclosures already provide robust and transparent information on these matters.&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board recommends a vote&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font>&#160;the stockholder proposal regarding additional reporting on child labor.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">35</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU11"></a>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_THIRTEEN"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_THIRTEEN"></a>PROPOSAL THIRTEEN</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING ADDITIONAL REPORTING ON WATER RISK</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT7"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STMT7"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">WHEREAS<font style="font-weight:normal;">: According to the 2021 IPCC report, climate change is intensifying the water cycle, resulting in more intense droughts globally. Climate change related water scarcity poses material risks to our company, including disruption of operations or lowered production capacity; disruption of supply chains; and political and legal risks related to competition for water resources.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla&#8217;s manufacturing operations require large amounts of water. Tesla operates in California and Nevada, where water rights are contentious; in Austin, Texas, where droughts are becoming more frequent, and in water-impacted areas of Shanghai and Germany. All these regions have medium to high risk of water stress.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla&#8217;s factory location choices have caused public upset and reputational damage. Tesla recently opened a factory in Berlin-Brandenburg, an increasingly water depleted region.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> The facility, which will use as much water as a 30,000 person town, is sited on a drinking water protection zone and has raised intense public concern.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">,</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> Hours after authorities gave approval for Tesla to begin production, a judge ruled that the assessment of Tesla&#8217;s planned water use had not been thorough.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup> Tesla&#8217;s Austin facility is the second largest factory globally; communities are raising concerns over the pressure Tesla will put on Austin&#8217;s long-term water supply.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">6</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Increased transparency may reveal shortcomings in Tesla&#8217;s water planning, risk assessment, and siting policies. For instance, Tesla&#8217;s ability to successfully continue and expand operations at its Gigafactory in Berlin-Brandenburg may be water limited. The region&#8217;s water utility company identified water risk that could jeopardize the factory&#8217;s expansion.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">7</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">,</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">8</sup><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Peer companies GM, Ford, and Fiat Chrysler have developed water stewardship standards and report on water resource management including responding to CDP water. Tesla does not respond to CDP water requests, receiving an &#8216;F&#8217; score annually since 2016.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">9</sup><font style="color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla does report water reduction activities at certain facilities and shows that new factories will have a lower overall water withdrawal intensity than most peers. However, Tesla fails to provide facility-specific water reduction targets or use data; identify water risk at each location; assess and disclose supply chain related water risk; describe measures to reduce or avoid siting of facilities in high water risk areas; or describe its broader water risk management strategy.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">RESOLVED<font style="font-weight:normal;">: Shareholders request the Board assess and report its ongoing water risk exposure, and all policies and practices to reduce this risk, from siting of facilities to preparing for water supply reductions associated with climate change, using quantitative indicators where appropriate.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">SUPPORTING STATEMENT<font style="font-weight:normal;">: At management discretion, Proponents request reporting of:</font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
